-- Colombia’s Banco GNB Sudameris Plans Bond Meetings Next Week
-- B y   D r e w   B e n s o n
-- 2012-07-13T18:03:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-13/colombia-s-banco-gnb-sudameris-plans-bond-meetings-next-week.html
Banco GNB Sudameris, a Colombian
lender, will hold meetings with bond investors next week and may
sell global dollar debt after the talks, according to a person
familiar with the plan.  The meetings are scheduled to begin July 16 and conclude
July 20, said the person, who asked not to be identified because
he’s not authorized to speak publicly. Bank of America Corp. is
arranging the meetings.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Drew Benson in  New York  at 
 abenson9@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
